The '''2008 Kyrgyzstan earthquake''' struck on October 5 at 21:52 local time (15:52 UTC) with a [[Moment magnitude scale|moment magnitude]] of 6.6, killing 75 people, including 41 children,<ref name="canberra">{{cite news|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/news/local/news/general/choppers-pick-up-quake-injured/1328079.aspx|title=Choppers pick up quake injured|last=Namatbayeva|first=Tolkun|date=2008-10-08|publisher=Canberra Times|accessdate=2008-10-09}}</ref> and injuring 150 people, including 93 children.<ref name="AP">{{cite news|url=http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5gpjxAG8LCJBug7O-__0DZol8F-BgD93LMTP01|title=Kyrgyzstan mourns after quake kills at least 74|date=2008-10-07|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=2008-10-09|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081011003409/http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5gpjxAG8LCJBug7O-__0DZol8F-BgD93LMTP01 |archivedate = October 11, 2008|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://eng.24.kg/community/2008/10/08/6254.html|title=150 injured, 74 dead in Nura village, emergencies ministry says|date=2008-10-08|publisher=24 Kyrgyzstan|accessdate=2008-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722135839/http://eng.24.kg/community/2008/10/08/6254.html|archive-date=2011-07-22|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> The center of the [[earthquake]] was near the town of [[Nura, Kyrgyzstan|Nura]], which was destroyed in the quake.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/7653979.stm|title=Deadly earthquake hits Kyrgyzstan|date=October 6, 2008|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=2008-10-10| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081009041634/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/7653979.stm| archivedate= 9 October 2008 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> The shock destroyed 100 buildings in the area and destroyed the nearby village of Kura.<ref name="Saralayeva">{{cite news|url=http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5gpjxAG8LCJBug7O-__0DZol8F-BgD93L1V401|title=Earthquake kills at least 72 in Kyrgyzstan|last=Saralayeva|first=Leila|date=2008-10-06|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=2008-10-06|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081009220734/http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5gpjxAG8LCJBug7O-__0DZol8F-BgD93L1V401 |archivedate = October 9, 2008|deadurl=yes}}</ref> Minor damage also occurred in nearby [[Xinjiang|Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region]]. The quake was felt throughout [[Central Asia]].<ref name="Saralayeva"/> A magnitude 5.7 [[aftershock]] in Xinjiang<ref>{{cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsww/Quakes/us2008xua1.php#details|title=Magnitude 5.7 - SOUTHERN XINJIANG, CHINA|date=October 5, 2008|publisher=USGS|accessdate=2008-10-10|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081006135241/http://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsww/Quakes/us2008xua1.php#details |archivedate = October 6, 2008|deadurl=yes}}</ref> and a magnitude 5.1 aftershock in Kyrgyzstan<ref name="AP"/> followed the earthquake. Two more aftershocks above magnitude 5 in Kyrgyzstan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsww/Quakes/us2008ycaw.php|title=Magnitude 5.1 - KYRGYZSTAN|date=October 13, 2008|publisher=USGS|accessdate=2008-10-19}}{{dead link|date=September 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsww/Quakes/us2008yca9.php|title=Magnitude 5.3 - KYRGYZSTAN|date=October 13, 2008|publisher=USGS|accessdate=2008-10-19|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081017174903/http://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsww/Quakes/us2008yca9.php |archivedate = October 17, 2008|deadurl=yes}}</ref> and one in Xinjiang<ref>{{cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/eqcenter/recenteqsww/Quakes/us2008ycax.php|title=Magnitude 5.1 - SOUTHERN XINJIANG, CHINA|date=October 13, 2008|publisher=USGS|accessdate=2008-10-19}}{{dead link|date=September 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> struck on October 13, UTC time. Victims were transported in military [[helicopter]]s to hospitals in [[Osh]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/07/world/asia/07quake.html|title=Quake Kills at Least 72 in Kyrgyzstan |last=Stern|first=David L.|date=2008-10-06|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=2008-10-09| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20151203135206/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/07/world/asia/07quake.html| archivedate=December 3, 2015<!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>

The [[Kyrgyzstan Emergency Ministry]] said that few buildings remained standing in the village: "Almost all buildings in the village have been destroyed. The only buildings remaining are the properly [[Earthquake engineering|engineered]] ones which were built recently: the [[school]] and a medical clinic."<ref name=canberra/> Kanatbek Abdrakhmatov, head of the [[Institute of Seismology]], attributed much of the destruction due to inferior construction of the buildings, many of which were built out of clay and straw.<ref name=canberra/>

The injured were paid 5,000 [[Kyrgyzstani som]]s ([[US$]] 136) and 3 tons of [[coal]], and families of the dead received 50&nbsp;kg of [[flour]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://eng.24.kg/community/2008/10/09/6272.html|title=Kyrgyz government allocates 36mln KGS for earthquake victims support|last=Kutueva|first=Aizada|date=2008-10-09|publisher=24 Kyrgyzstan|accessdate=2008-10-09|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081029012339/http://eng.24.kg/community/2008/10/09/6272.html|archivedate=2008-10-29|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> 200 people wish to remain in Nura, and were provided with 100 6-person [[tent]]s.<ref name="kyr">{{cite news|url=http://eng.24.kg/community/2008/10/08/6259.html|title=New houses for earthquake victims to be built in spring 2009|last=Cheban|first=Olga|date=2008-10-08|publisher=24 Kyrgyzstan|accessdate=2008-10-09|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081029005734/http://eng.24.kg/community/2008/10/08/6259.html|archivedate=2008-10-29|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> 100 mobile homes are being transported to Nura, and the village will be rebuilt in the spring of 2009, and should be completed by August 2009.<ref name="kyr"/> [[Uzbekistan]] pledged the equivalent of US$200,000 in humanitarian aid, including 120 tons of [[cement]], as well as other building materials.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.turkishweekly.net/news.php?id=60052|title=Uzbekistan to provide humanitarian aid worth US$200,000 to Kyrgyz Republic|date=2008-10-09|publisher=Turkish Weekly|accessdate=2008-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303212101/http://www.turkishweekly.net/news.php?id=60052|archive-date=2016-03-03|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

In Kyrgyzstan, an official day of mourning was observed on October 7, 2008.<ref name="AP"/>

