'''Abolla''' ({{lang-grc|Ἄβολλα}}), was a city of [[Sicily]], mentioned only by [[Stephanus Byzantinus]], who affords no clue to its position, but it has been supposed, on account of the resemblance of the name, to have occupied the site of [[Avola]], between [[Syracuse, Sicily|Syracuse]] and [[Noto]]. A coin of this city has been published by {{ill|Jacques Philippe d'Orville|fr}} (''Sicula'', pt. ii. tab. 20), but is of very uncertain authority. ([[Joseph Hilarius Eckhel|Eckhel]], vol. i. p. 189 ; Castell., ''Sicil. Vet. Num.'' p. 4.)

