'''Laguna del Carbón''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for "coal lagoon") is a [[salt lake]] in [[Corpen Aike Department]], [[Santa Cruz Province, Argentina|Santa Cruz Province]], [[Argentina]]. This salt lake is located {{convert|54|km|abbr=off}} from [[Puerto San Julián]], within the ''Gran Bajo de San Julián'' (Great San Julián Depression), an [[endorheic basin]] situated between the [[San Julian Bay]] and the [[Chico River (Santa Cruz)|Chico River]]. At {{convert|105|m}} below [[sea level]], Laguna del Carbón is the [[Extremes on Earth|lowest point]] of [[Argentina]] and both the [[Western Hemisphere|Western]] and [[Southern Hemisphere|Southern]] [[Earth|Hemispheres]], and the [[lowest point on Earth|seventh-lowest point on Earth]].<ref>{{cite web | author=David K. Lynch | title=Land Below Sea Level | url=http://geology.com/below-sea-level/ | publisher= Geology.com | accessdate=2009-09-29}}</ref>

As in several other locations in [[Patagonia]], [[dinosaur]] [[fossil]]s have been found in the area.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Griffin |first=Miguel |author2=Pastorino, Guido |title=The Genus Trophon Monfort, 1810 (Gastropoda: Muricidae) In The Tertiary Of Patagonia |journal=[[Journal of Paleontology]] |volume=79 |issue=2 |pages=296–311 |doi=10.1666/0022-3360(2005)079<0296:tgtmgm>2.0.co;2 |date=Mar 2005 |url=http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa3790/is_200503/ai_n11827026/pg_7 |accessdate=2 September 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090518054505/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa3790/is_200503/ai_n11827026/pg_7/ |archivedate=18 May 2009 |df= }}</ref>

